The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 January is 29,587 (3,424.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 January, there were 5,289 new confirmed cases (612.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 January, there were 6,066 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 13% (777 fewer cases).
